definition.value: A beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
A monoterpenyl phosphate that is the O-diphospho derivative of (+)-borneol.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and D-glucitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylglucose consisting of an beta-L-fucopyranose residue and a beta-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.

A branched pentasaccharide consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with an alpha-D-Man-(1->6)-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4) linkage.
A D-altrofuranose in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
